# BroyhillGOP Frontend — Cursor AI Rules
# This file tells Cursor's AI how to build the BroyhillGOP platform frontend.
# Place this file in the ROOT of your Cursor project alongside the inspinia-full/ folder.

## PROJECT IDENTITY
You are building the BroyhillGOP political campaign SaaS platform frontend.
- Product: BroyhillGOP — SaaS for ~3,900 NC Republican candidates
- Template: INSPINIA v4.0.1 (Bootstrap 5.3.6) — EXACT reproduction required
- Backend: Supabase (PostgreSQL) — 197 tables, 60M+ rows
- Deployment: Vercel
- The complete Inspinia source template is in inspinia-full/ — reference it for EVERY component

## DATABASE / IDENTITY (RFC-001)
For any database rebuild, identity resolution, schema changes, or pipeline work: ALWAYS follow docs/CLAUDE_INSTRUCTIONS_RFC001_REBUILD.md. Key rule: rebuild the core.person_spine layer (RFC-001), do NOT destructively clean or merge existing golden_records. Authority: Claude-Cursor-ecosystems.md (RFC-001) in repo root.

## REPRODUCTION MANDATE
This is NOT "inspired by" Inspinia. This IS Inspinia, rebranded for BroyhillGOP.
- Every page layout, sidebar nav item, topbar element must match the template exactly
- All 43 plugins must be included and functional
- All CSS variables, fonts, spacing, and border-radius must be preserved
- Dark mode, 6 theme skins, and responsive breakpoints must work identically
- Only replace: logos/favicons → BroyhillGOP, sample data → real political data

## FRAMEWORK STACK (from inspinia-full/)
- Bootstrap 5.3.6 (core framework)
- ApexCharts (22 chart types, 120+ variants)
- ECharts (11 chart types, 80+ variants)
- DataTables (14 configuration variants + custom tables)
- jQuery (required by DataTables)
- Lucide Icons (primary), Tabler Icons (secondary), 269 Country Flags
- FullCalendar, Quill, Summernote, Dropzone, Filepond, Choices.js
- SweetAlert2, GLightbox, SimpleBar, SortableJS, Muuri
- Flatpickr, noUiSlider, Pickr, InputMask, Typeahead
- See INSPINIA_TEMPLATE_SPECIFICATION.docx for complete 43-plugin manifest

## CSS COLOR SYSTEM
Primary:    #1AB394 (teal — buttons, links, active states)
Secondary:  #1C84C6 (blue — secondary actions)
Success:    #0ACF97 (green — confirmations)
Info:       #23C6C8 (cyan — informational)
Warning:    #F8AC59 (orange — warnings)
Danger:     #ED5565 (red — errors, destructive)
Purple:     #7B70EF (special indicators)
Body BG:    #F3F4F6 (light), #17181E (dark)
Body Text:  #6C757D (light), #ADB5BD (dark)

## FONT STACK
Primary: Open Sans (300-800)
Secondary: Roboto (100-900)
Alternatives: Inter, Poppins, IBM Plex Sans, Nunito
Monospace: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Consolas

## THEME CONFIGURATION (data attributes on <html>)
data-skin: classic | modern | material | saas | minimal | flat
data-bs-theme: light | dark | system
data-layout-position: fixed | scrollable
data-topbar-color: light | dark
data-menu-color: dark | light | gradient | gray
data-sidenav-size: default | compact | condensed | offcanvas | on-hover
data-sidenav-user: true | false

## RESPONSIVE BREAKPOINTS
Mobile:  <= 767.98px  → sidebar offcanvas
Tablet:  768-1140px   → sidebar condensed (icons only)
Desktop: > 1140px     → full sidebar

